==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}

Zhang (2021): {{Han compound|今|alt1=亼|心|ls=ic|t1=upside-down mouth|t2=heart}}: to listen to one's heart.<ref>張富海：《利用諧聲構擬上古音應該註意的幾個問題》，《出土文獻》，2021年第1期，頁134。)</ref> Original character for {{och-l|念|to think}}.

''{{w|Shuowen}}'' interprets {{och-l|今}} to be a phonetic component, but the Old Chinese phonetics do not match.

===Etymology===
{{zh-forms|alt=𫝹}}
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s-njam}}. Cognate with {{cog|bo|ཉམ}}, {{m|bo|ཉམས||soul, mind, heart}}, {{m|bo|སྙམ||to think, to feel}} ({{zh-ref|Quan, 1996}}). Related to {{och-l|恁|to think, to miss}}.

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} notes it may be an area word; compare {{cog|km|ចំណាំ||memory; recollection}}, {{cog|map-pro|*nəmnəm||to think}}.

